JOHANNESBURG – One of South Africa’s finest boxing trainers, Willie Lock, passed away on Thursday at the age of 84. 
	  
	Lock, born and bred in Benoni, has been battling with illness for some before he succumbed in his hometown. He led the way in transforming boxing and steered Peter ‘Terror’ Mathebula to the WBA flyweight title in Los Angeles in December 1980.  Mathebula became the first black South African fighter to win a world title. AFP